'''''Talar''''' was a material that could be used to tip [[Arrow/Legends|arrows]] used with [[Bow/Legends|bows]].<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> By [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'' represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> [[Kiran Tatch]], a [[Tunroth]] member of the [[Tunroth Hunter]]s cultural group and the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] group known as the [[Granse Confederacy]] who preferred to use low-technology [[Weapon/Legends|weaponry]], used ''talar''-tipped arrows with his ''[[klirun]]'' bow for stunning his targets.<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
''Talar'' was mentioned in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="AIR" />

